🌺 सत्संग-मुक्तावली

जब अनेक अनुभवी संत एक ही सत्य को अपनी-अपनी अनुभूति से प्रकाशित करते हैं, तब उनके वचन पुष्पों की भाँति एक दिव्य माला बन जाते हैं।

Living Vedanta Library preserves these living garlands of wisdom so that future seekers may experience not only the original scripture, but also its living reflection in the hearts of contemporary saints.

🌸 Today's Pearl

Today's discussion quietly teaches an entire path.

① Anil Kumar Sharma Ji begins...

भक्ति कठिन नहीं है।

The Lord never demanded impossible practices first.

He asks for

a simple heart,

honesty,

contentment,

and freedom from crookedness.

That is the doorway.

② Acharya Jayprakash Pandey Ji continues...

Once simplicity begins,

purification begins.

External purity has value,

but its purpose is to prepare us for

internal purity.

Hatred leaves.

Pride leaves.

Jealousy leaves.

Deceit leaves.

Then the immortal words become true—

निर्मल मन जन सो मोहि पावा।

③ Then Acharya Ji gives the warning

Why is this difficult?

Because we live in Kali Yuga.

Self-interest appears attractive.

Anger appears justified.

Greed appears intelligent.

Pretence appears respectable.

Therefore,

simplicity itself becomes tapas.

Truthfulness becomes courage.

Humility becomes heroism.

🌿 English Reflection

The saints have quietly described the entire spiritual path.

Devotion begins with simplicity.

Purification transforms the heart.

The challenges of Kali Yuga make this path difficult,

yet also make every sincere effort immensely valuable.

The Lord is not searching for perfection.

He is searching for sincerity.

A pure heart is His chosen dwelling.

🌺 Living Vedanta Reflection

The Yoga Vāsiṣṭha repeatedly teaches that bondage is born of the mind.

Today's satsang reveals how that bondage begins to dissolve.

Not through extraordinary miracles.

Not through complicated philosophy.

But through

simplicity,

purity,

truthfulness,

contentment,

and holy company.

When these mature,

Self-Knowledge shines naturally.

🌿 Satsang Pearls (सत्संग-मुक्तावली)

💎 भक्ति का प्रथम चरण सरलता है।

💎 सरलता से अन्तःकरण शुद्ध होता है।

💎 शुद्ध अन्तःकरण में आत्मज्ञान उदित होता है।

💎 आत्मज्ञान से कलियुग भी साधना का क्षेत्र बन जाता है।

💎 निर्मल हृदय में भगवान् को खोजने की आवश्यकता नहीं रहती—वे स्वयं प्रकट होते हैं।

